> Looking for a quick and tasty midweek dinner option? Try cooking up our Beef and Veg Stir-Fry in Black Bean Sauce in just 20 minutes for a delicious and speedy meal.

== Rice ==

Boil a full #kettle{}.

When boiling, pour the water into a large #saucepan{} with @salt{1/4%tsp} on high heat.
Add the @Jasmine Rice{150%g} and cook for ~{12-13%minutes}.

Drain in a #sieve{} and pop back in the pan. Cover with a #lid{} and leave to the side
until ready to serve.

== Prep ==

While the rice cooks, halve, peel and thinly slice the @onion{1}(thinly sliced).

Trim the @green beans{150%g}.

Peel and grate the @garlic{2%cloves}(grated) (or use a #garlic press{}).

Roughly chop the @salted peanuts{25%g}(roughly chopped).

== Stir-Fry ==

Heat a drizzle of @oil{drizzle} in a large #frying pan{} on medium-high heat.

When the oil is hot, add the @British beef mince{240%g} and cook until browned,
~{5-6%minutes}. Use a #spoon{} to break it up as it cooks, then drain and discard
any excess fat.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw mince. The mince
> is cooked when no longer pink in the middle.

Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Add the garlic, onion and green beans to the beef and stir-fry until softened
slightly, ~{5-6%minutes}.

Add in the @sugar snap peas{80%g} and stir-fry for ~{1%minute} more.

== Sauce ==

Stir in the @black bean sauce{150%g} and @water{50%ml}, then bring to the boil.

Cook until the sauce has thickened, ~{1%minute}, then remove from the heat.

Taste and season with @salt{} and @pepper{} if needed.

== To Serve ==

Fluff up the rice with a #fork{}, then share between your #bowls{}.

Top with the beef and veg stir-fry, making sure you get all the black bean
sauce from the pan.

Sprinkle over the peanuts to finish for those who'd like them. Enjoy!